{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"steal","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"len"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gsize","text":"gsize","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">! = nil) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"?>!"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that if the array is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NULL"},{"type":"text","text":" terminated this may still return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if the length of the array was zero and pdata was not yet"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"allocated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even if set, the [callback"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DestroyNotify","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] function will never be called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the current contents of the array and the caller is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"responsible for freeing the array elements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An example of use:"}]},{"syntax":"c","type":"codeListing","code":["`g_autoptr(GPtrArray)` chunk_buffer = g_ptr_array_new_with_free_func (g_bytes_unref);","","\/\/ Some part of your application appends a number of chunks t